nib.text:
A man was killed in a shooting Wednesday evening in south Minneapolis, police said.

MPD officers responded to a report of a person shot on the 1700 block of East Lake Street just after 6 p.m.

When they arrived, officers found a man, believed to be in his 30s, with a gunshot wound.

The man was pronounced deceased at the scene.

Investigators believe the victim was targeted. 

A police spokesman said there was no further threat to the public.

Police said a suspect fled the area and they were checking for video evidence of the shooting.

The investigation is ongoing.

nib.text:
A standoff with police ended peacefully in north Minneapolis Wednesday afternoon after an armed robbery suspect surrendered to officers.

According to MPD police spokesman John Elder, the man robbed a tobacco store in St. Paul around noon.

After the robbery, St. Paul police attempted to pull the man over but he evaded them and headed west into Minneapolis. 

The man was traveling at a high rate of speed and eventually crashed his vehicle near Newton Avenue and North 29th Street.

At that point, the man reportedly threatened officers and refused to get out of his vehicle.

Additional specialized units from the Hennepin County Sheriff's Office responded to the scene and residents were advised to avoid the area.

After approximately four hours, the man surrendered to negotiators, Elder said.

The man was transported to an area hospital for minor injuries sustained in the crash.

No other injuries were reported. 

St. Paul police will be in charge of the ongoing investigation.
